---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="2026 Portfolio Stress-Test | Arkadi Avanesyan" description="Free checklist to identify hidden risks in your portfolio before the next market crash.">
  <section class="pt-32 pb-16 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Header -->
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-red-100 text-red-700 text-sm font-medium rounded-full mb-4">Free Resource</span>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">
          Is Your Portfolio Ready for a 20% Drop?
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-600">
          Use this checklist to identify hidden risks in your current holdings before the market turns.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <article class="card">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-red-100 flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span class="text-sm text-red-600 font-medium">2026 Stress-Test</span>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Portfolio Risk Checklist</h2>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="text-slate-600 mb-8">
          Most investors don't realize their portfolio is "fragile" until a crash has already started. The S&P 500 experiences drawdowns exceeding 20% roughly once every 5-7 years. Use this checklist to stress-test your holdings today.
        </p>

        <!-- Checklist Section 1 -->
        <div class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-6 h-6 bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm">1</span>
            Concentration Risk
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 pl-8">
            <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer">
              <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 w-4 h-4 rounded border-slate-300 text-blue-600 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-slate-700">No single position exceeds 10% of my portfolio</span>
            </label>
            <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer">
              <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 w-4 h-4 rounded border-slate-300 text-blue-600 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-slate-700">No single sector exceeds 25% of my portfolio</span>
            </label>
            <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer">
              <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 w-4 h-4 rounded border-slate-300 text-blue-600 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-slate-700">I have exposure to at least 3 uncorrelated asset classes</span>
            </label>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Checklist Section 2 -->
        <div class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-6 h-6 bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm">2</span>
            Liquidity Risk
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 pl-8">
            <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer">
              <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 w-4 h-4 rounded border-slate-300 text-blue-600 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-slate-700">I can liquidate 80% of my portfolio within 24 hours</span>
            </label>
            <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer">
              <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 w-4 h-4 rounded border-slate-300 text-blue-600 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-slate-700">I have 3-6 months of expenses in cash or equivalents</span>
            </label>
            <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer">
              <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 w-4 h-4 rounded border-slate-300 text-blue-600 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-slate-700">I don't hold illiquid assets I might need to sell in a downturn</span>
            </label>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Checklist Section 3 -->
        <div class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-6 h-6 bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm">3</span>
            Behavioral Risk
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 pl-8">
            <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer">
              <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 w-4 h-4 rounded border-slate-300 text-blue-600 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-slate-700">I can watch my portfolio drop 30% without panic-selling</span>
            </label>
            <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer">
              <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 w-4 h-4 rounded border-slate-300 text-blue-600 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-slate-700">I have a written plan for what to do in a market crash</span>
            </label>
            <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer">
              <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 w-4 h-4 rounded border-slate-300 text-blue-600 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-slate-700">I have cash reserved specifically to buy during crashes</span>
            </label>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Checklist Section 4 -->
        <div class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-6 h-6 bg-slate-900 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-sm">4</span>
            Structural Risk
          </h3>
          <div class="space-y-3 pl-8">
            <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer">
              <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 w-4 h-4 rounded border-slate-300 text-blue-600 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-slate-700">I understand the beta of each position relative to the market</span>
            </label>
            <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer">
              <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 w-4 h-4 rounded border-slate-300 text-blue-600 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-slate-700">I have at least one "antifragile" position that benefits from volatility</span>
            </label>
            <label class="flex items-start gap-3 cursor-pointer">
              <input type="checkbox" class="mt-1 w-4 h-4 rounded border-slate-300 text-blue-600 focus:ring-blue-500" />
              <span class="text-slate-700">My portfolio's maximum drawdown in 2008/2020 scenarios is acceptable to me</span>
            </label>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Score Section -->
        <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-slate-900 mb-3">How did you score?</h3>
          <div class="space-y-2 text-sm">
            <p class="text-slate-600"><span class="font-semibold text-green-600">10-12 checks:</span> Your portfolio is well-prepared for market stress.</p>
            <p class="text-slate-600"><span class="font-semibold text-yellow-600">6-9 checks:</span> You have some vulnerabilities that could cause problems.</p>
            <p class="text-slate-600"><span class="font-semibold text-red-600">0-5 checks:</span> Your portfolio may be more fragile than you think.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Key Insight -->
        <div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-4 mb-8">
          <p class="text-slate-700">
            <strong>The reality:</strong> Most portfolios are designed to grow in bull markets, not survive bear markets. The items you couldn't check represent the structural flaws that cause panic-selling when crashes happen.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- CTA Section -->
      <div class="mt-8 card bg-slate-900 text-white border-0">
        <div class="text-center">
          <p class="text-slate-400 text-sm font-medium mb-2">Free Live Implementation Lab</p>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">Want Help Fixing These Gaps?</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6 max-w-xl mx-auto">
            I'm running a free hands-on workshop where we'll stress-test your specific portfolio together and build a crisis-proof allocation. This is a live session, not a recording.
          </p>
          <ul class="text-slate-400 text-sm mb-6 space-y-1">
            <li>Run live stress-tests on your asset allocation</li>
            <li>Build a "Crisis-Proof" dashboard together</li>
            <li>Get direct feedback on your hedging strategy</li>
          </ul>
          <a
            href="https://maven.com/p/62cecb/build-your-first-crisis-proof-portfolio"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-white text-slate-900 font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-full hover:bg-slate-100 transition-colors"
          >
            Join the Free Live Workshop
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
            </svg>
          </a>
          <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs mt-4">March 12, 2026 · 45 min · Limited seats</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Back Link -->
      <div class="mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/tutorials" class="text-slate-500 hover:text-slate-700 text-sm">
          ← Back to Tutorials
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
